In this proclamation, President Barack Obama recognizes November as National Diabetes Month. He highlights the impact of diabetes on millions of Americans and the serious health complications it can cause. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of supporting healthy lifestyles and raising awareness about diabetes. It also mentions the different types of diabetes and the risk factors associated with them. The President expresses his commitment to finding a cure for both type 1 and type 2 diabetes and investing in research to prevent the disease and improve care. The proclamation acknowledges the Affordable Care Act's provisions to ensure coverage for individuals with pre-existing conditions like diabetes. It also highlights First Lady Michelle Obama's Let's Move! initiative, which aims to address childhood obesity and reduce the risk of diabetes among young people. The President calls upon various organizations and individuals to participate in activities that promote diabetes awareness and prevention.